Deck.gl heatmap layer

The heatmap layer displays observations distribution as a heatmap overlay provided by deck.gl.

The radius, intensity, threshold and opacity arguments can be used to customize the heatmap appearance.

import polars as pl
from pylifemap import Lifemap

# Load iucn dataset
iucn = pl.read_parquet(
    "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Lifemap-ToL/pylifemap/main/data/iucn.parquet"
)

(
    Lifemap(iucn)
    .layer_heatmap_deck(opacity=0.5)
    .show()
)
Warning: 777 taxids have not been found in Lifemap database.
Warning: 152 duplicated taxids have been found in the data.

For a detailed list of layer_heatmap_deck arguments you can take a look at its documentation.

For an alternative heatmap visualization, see layer_heatmap.
